posts.subject: Raspberry Pi
posts.body:
This is not my blog.

  I am aware of many projects to do with a Raspberry Pi.  I own two of them.  Most of them are pretty gay, like the faggy weather station shit.
  I am not as literate as most of the rest of /tech/ when it comes to Linux, but I have some alternative ideas that I was thinking of.
  Some of my ideas are as follows:

     1.  Create a wireless Zeronet router
     2.  Create a wireless Tor Router (I used to have one, but I had erased the SD card and could never get one to work again - the instructions on how to do it do not work anymore for some reason)
     3.  Create a wireless camera where I can connect to the Pi via my phone over wireless, and watch a live video feed.

  If I am able to make any of these, I will create an .iso and just upload it onto here.  No problem.

  The wireless camera idea I had while driving back home today.  I was thinking about being 'nearby' a location but being able to watch a live video feed via my phone through the wireless signal that my Pi would put out.  No Routers Involved.  Just thinking tactically.
  I already had made a PirateBox and I had one of those 'Phone Charger Batteries' powering it while it was in my backpack.  
  The PirateBox worked well and stayed on for a long time, (12 to 18 hours I think?) but my point is that it can be powered by one of those batteries as long as it puts out 2A and 5V or something like that.
  So, creating a live camera like I described is do-able, even though I would have to pick up the camera when nobody is looking (when I'm done doing whatever it is I'm doing) so my idea is to incorporate something that the PirateBox offers along with utilizing the Raspberry Pi Camera to make this work.
  I would have to hide the camera in an object (after it's ready) that looked like a rock or something to make this the way I want though.  Chicken wire with paper mache' stuff.

  If anyone has any of these things made already, please provide an .iso .
